                       "mage":  3,
                       "race":  4,
                       "artifacts":  [

                                     ],
                       "description":  "<u>Sauron</u> is the Dark Lord returned, a will of iron that has never forgotten its claim. From Barad-dur he bends the lands through fear and patience, drawing all things toward a single purpose. He does not need love or loyalty, only obedience, and he will take it by force or by dread.<br><br>The hunt begins in the shadow of Minas Morgul, where the trail is secured and a relic of power is drawn from cursed ground. From there the march moves toward the Black Gate, where the first disciplined hosts take shape under a hard command.",
                       "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\">deck <i>Deck identity:</i> The broad machinery of Mordor: armies, monsters, tyranny, and corruption grinding forward through fear and accumulation.",
                       "banner": "banner_sauron_the_dark_eye",
                       "variants":  [
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_dark_eye",
                                            "displayName":  "The Dark Eye",
                                            "description":  "<u>The Dark Eye</u> burns above Barad-dur like a star of malice that never sets, sleepless over Gorgoroth, the Black Gate, and the dead roads beneath Ephel Duath. It is dread made watchful, a will that peers through palantiri, dreams, and trembling rumor until no secrecy feels safe and every hidden movement seems already betrayed.<br><br>This variant is built on exposure, fear, and a suffocating dominion that narrows the enemy's every choice.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\">deck <i>Deck identity:</i> The Eye watching through Nazgul terror: surveillance, revelation, dread, and command pressure that makes every movement feel seen.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_dark_eye",
                                            "banner": "banner_sauron_the_dark_eye"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_deceiver",
                                            "displayName":  "The Deceiver",
                                            "description":  "<u>The Deceiver</u> walks in the memory of the Second Age: Annatar, Lord of Gifts, whispering to the smiths of Eregion; corrupter of Celebrimbor's great labor; and dark counselor to the pride of Numenor in its final blasphemy. Fair-seeming, patient, and terrible in wisdom misused, he raises no banner at first, but teaches the mighty to forge their own chains until kingdoms drown, temples burn, and the bent world itself bears witness to his fraud.<br><br>This variant leans into deceit, seduction, false gifts, and the hidden mastery won long before the sword is drawn.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\">deck <i>Deck identity:</i> Sauron as Annatar and the Deceiver: false gifts, seductive promises, corrupted loyalties, and domination won through trust before open war.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_deceiver",
                                            "banner": "banner_sauron_the_deceiver"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_necromancer",
                                            "displayName":  "The Necromancer",
                                            "description":  "<u>The Necromancer</u> broods in Dol Guldur, and Greenwood the Great withers into Mirkwood beneath the shadow of his hidden throne. From that hill of sorcery crawl spiders, wraiths, and corrupted things, while fear seeps through root and branch until the very forest seems to remember some older terror returning from forgotten ages.<br><br>This variant favors haunted pressure, monstrous servants, dark sorcery, and corruption that lingers long after the first blow.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "<sprite name=\"deck\">deck <i>Deck identity:</i> Sauron as the Necromancer of Dol Guldur: ruin, occult infestation, cursed creatures, and slow supernatural decay spreading from dark strongholds.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_necromancer",
                                            "banner": "banner_sauron_the_necromancer"
                                        }
                                    ],
